The paper proposes a new model for recurrent neural networks that focuses on the memorization subtask. This is a common problem in many areas of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), computer vision (cs.CV), and natural language processing (cs.CL). Given that the proposed model and training algorithm are applicable to a wide range of sequential tasks, it is likely that the paper could be classified under any of these sub-categories. However, based on the content of the paper, we believe that cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories, followed by cs.NE, cs.CV, and cs.CL.
